r side-by-side comparison because it has been discontinued. You can still read our original review below, but Top Ten Reviews is no longer updating this product’s information.</em>","The Yamaha BD-S677 is an oddity among the <a href=\"/best-blu-ray-players\">3D Blu-ray players</a> we reviewed in that it&#39;s the only device to not offer Netflix streaming support. It&#39;s also one of the few players that doesn&#39;t include an app for Hulu Plus video streaming. The fact that it still places on our top 10 list of the best 3D Blu-ray players despite these two glaring omissions speaks volumes about its strengths elsewhere.","Considering that the Yamaha Corporation started out as an instrument manufacturer, it&#39;s no surprise that this particular 3D Blu-ray player earns a perfect score in audio performance and features. Not only does it satisfy your frustrated inner audiophile by playing SACDs, but it also has robust coverage to play a variety of disc types and audio files. In addition, it supports both DTS-HD Master Audio and Dolby TrueHD.","In terms of software, the Yamaha has a cleanly designed menu interface that&#39;s easy to navigate through. During our boot test, in which we measured how long it takes for a Blu-ray player to reach its home screen when turned on, the Yamaha topped our evaluated Blu-ray players with a mark of 2.1 seconds.","The thing is, few people buy Blu-ray players – particularly 3D Blu-ray players – for their audio prowess alone. Video performance has a great deal to do with the decision as well. Even though the S677 delivers on picture quality, it falls short on bonus capabilities that would make it a more desirable home theater inclusion like 4K upscaling, in case you finally decide to buy a 4K TV, and 2D to 3D conversion for those occasions when you&#39;re feeling experimental.","The player does score bonus points for including Miracast compatibility, which lets you stream media from another Miracast-enabled smartphone or tablet in the vicinity. The added availability of an Android and iOS app to turn your smartphone into a remote control also helps. Its lack of Netflix or Hulu Plus is what hurts this player the most. Even though there is built-in support for YouTube and VUDU for video, Picasa for photos, and Dropbox for playback of cloud-based media files, this may be a shortcoming that you can’t overlook."]},"id":"6c696047-b626-4a50-99f1-740866599263","type":"text"},{"data":{"text":"Summary"},"id":"7e77d7d2-e74c-474a-88c7-cc69481657c7","type":"heading"},{"data":{"paragraphs":["Like a couple of other 3D Blu-ray players in our lineup, the Yamaha BD-S677 prioritizes audio performance over video versatility. It lacks a couple features that would create a complete streaming experience like support for several popular streaming apps. Still, its deep set of features and connectivity standards make it easy to integrate the Blu-ray player into your home theater setup."]},"id":"ae9c27cc-130c-4cda-85e1-8670735cf4fa","type":"text"}]],"body":null,"legacyId":"product_review_page_61093","url":"/yamaha-bd-review","authors":[{"email":"","slug":"jonathan-knoder","url":"/author/jonathan-knoder","dateCreated":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","name":"Jonathan Knoder","dateModified":"2019-04-16T16:01:12Z","id":"yRHneGGUztMrGu99zxra6M","dateImported":null,"site":"toptenreviews"}],"territories":["US","GB"],"companies":[],"dateCreated":"2014-11-07T16:59:45Z","datePublished":"2014-11-07T16:59:45Z","name":"Yamaha BD-S677","synopsis":"Editor’s Note: This product has been removed from our side-by-side comparison because it has been discontinued.","review":{"rating":82,"verdict":"The Yamaha BD-S677 has limited versatility, but the Blu-ray player still has the features and specifications needed to be a strong foundation for your home theater.","pros":["The Yamaha BD-S677 features a stellar set of audio playback standards."],"cons":["It is hindered by its lack of access to Netflix streaming."]},"strapline":"Editor’s Note: This product has